-- Lakers Plan to Exercise Option on Andrew Bynum, L.A. Times Says
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-03-20T04:05:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/lakers-plan-to-exercise-option-on-andrew-bynum-l-a-times-says.html
The Los Angeles Lakers plan to
exercise a $16.1 million option for the last year of All-Star
center  Andrew Bynum ’s contract, the Los Angeles Times reported,
citing General Manager Mitch Kupchak.  The Lakers have until June 30 to exercise their option, the
paper said. Bynum, 24, would become a free agent after next
season unless he negotiates a contract extension.  Bynum has averaged 18.1 points and 12.9 rebounds this
season. In 10 games this month, he’s boosted his averages to 24
points and 13.1 rebounds while shooting 65.7 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
